The satellite in space receives the call and reflects it back to Earth almost immediately.
The satellite was launched into space by a rocket. Scientists use telescopes in space because the atmosphere of the Earth distorts light and vision.
You need a giant rocket over 100 feet tall to put a satellite or a telescope in space.
