If you've seen the movie National Treasure, you may think that the treasure map was drawn on the back of the Declaration of Independence.
But that is not true. Though at the back of the document there is a written statement, it is not an archive.
On the back of the Declaration of Independence were the words: "Original Declaration of Independence dated July 4, 1776".
Although it is not known who wrote it, it is known that in the early days of its existence the large parchment document (its dimensions are 29¾ inches by 24½ inches) was rolled up to keep it in storage.
The note was added as a tag.
