Among popular sports are football, basketball, volleyball, water polo, fencing, rugby, cycling, ice hockey, roller hockey and auto racing.
Wintersports are most popular in the northern regions, so Italians compete in international competitions and Olympic events.
Japan has approximately 6,800 islands (the largest being Honshu), making it the 7th largest island in the world.
Due to the group/cluster of islands that Japan has, Japan is often called, in a geographical sense, an archipelago.
The beginning of Taiwan started early in the 15th century, when European sailors recorded the name of the island as Ilha Formosa, or beautiful island.
1624 Dutch East India Company establishes a base in southwestern Taiwan, transforming the indigenous methods of rice production and hiring Chinese workers to work in its rice and sugar plantations.
In 1683, the Qing dynasty occupied the western and northern coastal areas of Taiwan and proclaimed Taiwan a province of the Qing Empire in 1885.
In 1895, after the defeat in the First Sino-Japanese War (1894–1895), the Qing government signed the Treaty of Shimonoseki, by which it ceded sovereignty over Taiwan to Japan, which ruled the island until 1945.
Machu Picchu consists of three major structures: Intihuatana, the Temple of the Sun and the Room of Three Windows.
Most of the buildings on the sides of the complex were reconstructed to give tourists a better impression of how they originally looked.
By 1976, 30 percent of Machu Picchu had been restored and the restoration continues to this day.
For example, the most common format in the world for taking still images is 35mm, which was the dominant film size at the end of the era of analogue film.
It is still manufactured today, but, what is more important, its proportions were inherited from the sensor formats of digital cameras.
The 35 mm format is actually, somewhat confusingly, 36 mm wide and 24 mm high.
The ratio of this format (divided by twelve to get the simplest integer ratio) is therefore called 3:2.
Several popular formats (e.g. APS) are equal to or very close to this ratio.
The much-maligned and often-ridiculed rule of thirds is simply a guideline that creates dynamism, maintaining a measure of order in a picture.
It states that the most effective location of the main subject is at the intersection of lines that divide the image into thirds vertically and horizontally (see example).
