There was also an era of division of provinces between dynasties. The most famous such period was the Three Kingdoms period, which lasted for 60 years between the Han and Jin dynasties.
In these periods fierce fighting took place between many nobles struggling for the throne.
The Three Kingdoms was one of the bloodiest periods in the history of Ancient China, thousands of people died fighting for a seat on the highest throne in the great palace in Xi'an.
