His views on all subjects of science, including psychology, were accepted.
As knowledge of Greek declined, the West became increasingly disconnected from its Greek philosophical and scientific roots.
Many observed rhythms in physiology and behavior often critically depend on the presence of endogenous cycles and how the biological clock produces them.
Periodic rhythms that do not simply respond to external periodic stimuli have been documented in most living organisms, including bacteria, fungi, plants, and animals.
Biological clocks are self-sustaining oscillators that continue a period of repeating self-sustained activity even in the absence of external stimuli.
The Hershey-Chase experiment was one of the key pieces of evidence that DNA is the genetic material.
Hershey and Chase used bacteriophages, or viruses, to insert their DNA into a bacterium.
They conducted two experiments, labeling either the DNA of the bacteriophage with radioactive phosphorus or the protein of the bacteriophage with radioactive sulfur.
Mutations can have a spectrum of effects depending on the type of mutation, the size of the genetic material involved, and whether the cells involved are gametes.
Only mutations in the germ cells can be passed to children, while mutations in other cells can cause cell death or cancer.
Nature-based tourism attracts people interested in visiting natural areas to enjoy the view, including flora and fauna.
Among the examples of local action are hunting, fishing, photography, birdwatching and visiting and studying information about the ecosystem.
An example is visiting Borneo and photographing and learning about orangutans.
Every morning, people leave their homes by car to go to their workplaces, and they are overtaken by other people, whose goal is the place they have just left.
In this dynamic car sharing everyone in one way or another is involved and contributing to a transport system based on the use of private cars.
Science now suggests that this mass carbon economy has moved the biosphere from one of its stable states that has supported human development for the past two million years.
Every person participates in society and uses transportation systems. Almost everyone complains about transportation systems.
In developed countries, you rarely hear similar complaints about the quality of water or the collapse of bridges.
Why are transportation systems so prone to complaints, why do they fail every day? Are transportation engineers simply incompetent?
Traffic flow is the study of the movement of individual drivers and vehicles between two points and the interactions that occur between them.
Unfortunately, studying traffic flow is difficult, because it is impossible to predict the behavior of a driver with one hundred percent certainty.
Fortunately, drivers tend to behave within a fairly uniform arrangement; so traffic flows strive for some moderate uniformity and can be approximately represented mathematically.
To better present the flow of traffic, relations have been established between the three main characteristics: (1) flow, (2) density, and (3) speed.
These relationships help plan, develop and operate road infrastructure.
Insects were the first animals to fly, and their ability to fly allowed them to avoid predators and find food and mates more efficiently.
Most insects have the advantage of being able to fold their wings along the body.
This provides them with a wider range of small hiding places from predators.
Today the only insects that cannot fold their wings are butterflies and dragonflies.
