The Amazon River is the second-longest river in the world and has more water than the second-longest river.
The Amazon River is also the widest river in the world, sometimes reaching six miles wide.
Full 20 percent of the water that flows into the oceans from the rivers of the planet comes from the Amazon.
The main river Amazon is 6387 km (3980 miles) long. It gathers water from thousands of smaller rivers.
Although the construction of stone pyramids continued until the end of the Old Kingdom, no one was ever able to surpass the pyramids of Giza in size and technical skill of their construction.
The Egyptians of the New Kingdom were impressed by the monuments of their predecessors, which had then more than a thousand years old.
The population of Vatican City is approximately 800 people. It is the smallest independent state in the world and the state with the smallest population.
The Vatican City uses Italian language in its laws and official communications.
Italian is also the everyday language used by most of those who work in the state, while Latin is often used in religious ceremonies.
All citizens of the Vatican are Catholics.
People have known the basic chemical elements — such as gold, silver and copper — since antiquity, as these are found in nature in a basic form and are relatively easy to extract with primitive tools.
Aristotle believed that all matter consists of a mixture of one or more of the four elements: earth, water, air, and fire.
It was more like the four states of matter (in the same order): solid, liquid, gaseous, and plasma, although he continued to theorize that they become new substances to form what we see.
Alloy is essentially a mixture of two or more metals.
Elements like calcium and potassium are considered metals.
Some alloys also contain small amounts of nonmetal elements, such as carbon.
