Severe weather is a general term for any weather phenomenon that can cause damage, significant social disruption, or loss of life.
Severe weather can occur anywhere in the world and it consists of various types, which depend on the location, the terrain and the atmospheric conditions.
Winds, hail, torrential rains and forest fires are presentations and effects of severe weather, along with lightning storms, tornadoes, thunderstorms and cyclones.
Between regional and seasonal phenomena of severe weather are blizzards, snowstorms, winter storms and sandstorms.
It is highly advisable that travelers are aware of any risk of severe weather that may affect the area, as this can affect any travel plans.
