Christmas is one of the most important festivals of Christianity, celebrating the birth of Jesus Christ.
Non-believers living in Christian countries or elsewhere in the world have adopted many of the traditions of this feast.
Traditionally, the night before Easter is spent in prayer and fasting in order to prepare for the resurrection of Christ.
There are certainly Christian theological explanations for this tradition, but it could also be a pre-Christian ritual of spring and fertility.
On Saturday evening of Holy Week, many traditional churches hold a vigil and the parishioners celebrate the Resurrection of Christ at midnight.
