Japanese work culture is more hierarchical and formal than what westerners are used to.
Costumes are the standard work attire and coworkers address each other by family names or job titles.
Harmony at work is most important, as well as an emphasis on team striving rather than praise of individual achievements.
Workers usually need to get the approval of their superiors for all decisions made and must obey the instructions without question.
